results.name: Black
results.title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Black
results.description:
The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Black provides a classic design that continues the tradition of perhaps one of the oldest athletic shoes in the history of footwear.

Although the history surrounding Converse began to take shape as early as 1917, the company designed the Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Black and similar models decades later as part of a tribute to the original shoe. The newer silhouette maintains many of the aesthetic aspects of its predecessor, but some of the fittings and materials have been updated as a way to make a robust shoe that Converse fans and footwear enthusiasts might be able to wear for decades to come. The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Black includes a premium canvas upper that is double-ply for extra strength and durability while the stitching near the toe is reinforced but designed to keep the classic look of the original. Converse added some extra padding to the insole in an effort to provide collectors or wearers with additional arch support and more cushioning for comfort.

The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Black released in January 2018 for $85.
results.model: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi

results.name: Comme des Garcons PLAY Black
results.title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY Black
results.description:
Japanese designer Rei Kawakubo is one of the most prolific fashion designers of all time. Aside from her Comme des Garçons collections, she has had numerous sneaker collaborations over the years. One of the most outstanding of these collaborations involves her different iterations of work modifying and styling up the Converse Chuck Taylor with her sub-label Comme des Garçons PLAY. Kawakubo’s first iteration of his Converse Chuck Taylors came about in 2009 when she modified the original by stripping back its contrast stitching. Six years later, in 2015, she took the All Star Chuck 70s as her template and created a shoe so beloved that it has been re-released every year since.

The most immediately recognizable thing in shoes from the Comme des Garçons PLAY line is their heart and eyes logo, originally conceived and created by Filip Pagowski. Unlike the original 2009 version, however, the 2015 version and every version thereafter has moved away from the original minimalist philosophy that inspired Kawakubo to start this line of collaborations. The Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Comme des Garçons PLAY harks back to the classic 70s Chuck Taylor style but with a high-top collar that snugly hugs the ankles and a black upper, white laces and a white sole and toe cap.

The Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Comme des Garçons PLAY Black was released in March of 2019 and retailed for $125.
results.model: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi

results.name: Off-White
results.title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Off-White
results.description:
PLEASE NOTE: US and UK sizing is the same for Converse All-Stars. Converse and Virgil Abloh’s Off-White teamed up once again to re-release the Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Off-White. This canvas model served as a follow-up to Abloh’s first Converse collaboration that was part of the "The Ten" collection.

While the all-white canvas upper of the Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Off-White draws similarities to classic non-collaborative colorways, there are many points of differentiation. To start, the black and white caution tape-themed midsole nods to one of Off-White’s key design motifs. Next, "Off-White™ for CONVERSE ‘CHUCK TAYLOR ALL-STAR’ Malden, Massachusetts USA c. 1917" is screen printed on the inside medial panel of the upper. To round out this Off-White Chuck Taylor, a modified star patch appears on the ankle and a signature orange zip-tie is hooked to the laces.

The Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Off-White originally released in October of 2018, and restocked in April of 2021, at a retail of $130.

results.title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Parchment
results.description:
The "Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Parchment" is a classic shoe paying homage to original Chuck Taylor All-Star from fifty years back. The parchment colorway in particular features a vintage-inspired off-white shade, reminiscent of aged parchment paper.

The shoe has high top silhouette with a classic minimalist design. The upper is constructed from canvas with reinforced stitching, a rubber toe cap, and a rubber outsole synonymous with most Converse shoes. It also maintains the red line that runs across the border of the midsole, signature All-Star tread pattern and the two eyelets on the inner side panel. Branding elements on the Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Parchment include the Converse All-Star logo on the ankle and the label behind the heel.

The Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Parchment was first released for retail at the price of $85 when it first debuted on January 1, 2018.

results.title: Converse Run Star Hike Ox White Black Gum
results.description:
The Converse Run Star Hike Ox White Black Gum is a reimagined version of the classic Chuck Taylor All Star.

A low-top sneaker, this shoe features a canvas upper highlighted with white stitching, metallic eyelets, and a rubber toe cap, details that stay true to the original Chucks. The upper for the White Black Gum Converse Run Star Hike Ox sits atop a chunky platform made with SmartFOAM® insoles that increase the shoe’s comfort level without adding any weight. Rounding off the design for this shoe is a two-tone rubber outsole and a rounded heel with a Star logo. Its outsole is split into two. Each half, hardened for durability, features rugged treads for improved traction.

The fashion-forward design of the Converse Run Star Hike Ox White Black Gum is what we find most exciting about this shoe. We also love that this shoe, released on July 22nd, 2020, for $105, is just as functional as it is appealing.

results.name: Comme des Garcons PLAY Egret Red Midsole
results.title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Egret Red Midsole
results.description:
The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Ox PLAY Egret Red Midsole is a variation of the Chuck Taylor All Star 70 by Converse in collaboration with Paris-based Japanese fashion label Comme des Garcons, commonly called CDG.

A low-top shoe, the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Ox PLAY Egret Red Midsole features an Egret White canvas upper detailed with metallic eyelets, pristine white stitching and laces, a black strip at the heel, and a CDG red-heart logo. This upper rests on a red midsole with high-profile rubber foxing, a diamond pattern around the round toe box, a white strip, and a Converse license plate patch. A rubber outsole, vulcanized for durability and patterned for grip, completes the build for this shoe.

At StockX, we think the design of the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Ox PLAY Egret Red Midsole is the best attribute of the shoe. Unique and detailed, this shoe’s design makes it pretty appealing. This shoe was released on March 24, 2022, retailing at $150.

results.description:
The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY Multi-Heart Black is part of the creative partnership of Converse and Comme des Garcons, a Tokyo-based streetwear label sought after for its deconstructed aesthetic and monochromatic colorways.

The sneaker takes the Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi silhouette and applies Comme des Garcons’ signature heart motifs to the black canvas upper. Each heart comes with eyes and features a bright red hue. Six hearts form a line above the rubber outsole on the later side, while the medial side panel only displays three hearts and the Converse All Star logo. The sneaker features seven pairs of metal eyelets that house off-white laces.

Our StockX experts appreciate the contrasting stitching on the upper, which comes in white thread. The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY Multi-Heart Black was launched on October 26th, 2023, and sold for $150.

results.description: The Converse Run Star Hike Ox Black White Gum is a stylish and versatile sneaker that combines the classic Converse design with modern features. The upper is made of durable canvas material, while the sole is made of a unique blend of rubber and foam for added comfort and support. The black and white colorway is timeless and easy to pair with any outfit, while the gum sole adds a touch of retro flair. Released on July 22, 2020, the Converse Run Star Hike Ox Black White Gum is priced at $105, making it an affordable option for those looking for a high-quality sneaker. The shoe is available in a range of sizes, ensuring a comfortable fit for everyone. Something we love about the Converse Run Star Hike Ox Black White Gum is its ability to seamlessly blend classic and modern design elements. Our experts think the best features of this shoe are its durable canvas upper, comfortable rubber and foam sole, and versatile black and white colorway. The standout feature of the Converse Run Star Hike Ox Black White Gum is its unique gum sole, which adds a touch of retro style to the overall design. Our experts especially love how easy it is to pair this sneaker with any outfit, making it a great addition to any wardrobe.
